Data attribution

The GeoJSON layers under `atlas/data/` are derived from the following public
sources; please retain attribution when redistributing derivative works:

  * OpenStreetMap contributors — © OSM, licensed under ODbL 1.0
    (base geometry, districts, protected-area polygons, waterways, canals,
    named peaks, industrial-area polygons)
  * Census of India 2011 — Registrar General of India
    (district demographics, urban centres, literacy, sex ratio, ST/SC %)
  * Rajasthan Forest Department, National Tiger Conservation Authority,
    Ramsar Convention Secretariat, UNESCO WHC — protected areas
  * IMD, ICAR, NBSS&LUP, ISRO SAC — climate, soils, vegetation, desertification
  * CGWB, CWC, RWRD, CADD — hydrology, dams, canals, groundwater, commands
  * GSI, DMG, IBM, HZL, HCL, RSMDC, Cairn — geology, minerals, mining, oil basins
  * DMICDC, RIICO, DoIC, MoCI, GI Registry — industry, SEZs, handicraft clusters
  * CEA, MNRE, NPCIL, SECI, RVUNL, RVPNL, RREC — energy, generation, grid
  * NITI Aayog, MoHUA, TAD Rajasthan — administrative overlays, smart cities

Per-feature citation chains live in each feature's `properties.source` field.
See docs/DATA_SOURCES.md for the complete source list and per-module reports
in docs/MODULE*_REPORT.md for module-specific provenance.
